      "A-III, B-I, C-IV, D-II",
      "A-IV, B-I, C-III, D-II",
      "A-IV, B-II, C-III, D-I",
      " A-III, B-II, C-IV, D-I"
    ],
    "correctOption": 0,
    "correctAnswer": null,
    "questionType": "MCQ",
    "marks": 4,
    "negativeMarks": -1,
    "subject": "Chemistry",
    "topic": "chemicals-in-foods",
    "difficulty": "easy",
    "solution": "<p>We can match the vitamins with their deficiency diseases as follows:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Vitamin A: Its deficiency causes Xerophthalmia, so A-III.</li><br/>\n<li>Thiamine (Vitamin B1): Its deficiency leads to Beri-Beri, so B-I.</li><br/>\n<li>Ascorbic acid (Vitamin C): Its deficiency causes Scurvy, so C-IV.</li><br/>\n<li>Riboflavin (Vitamin B2): Its deficiency leads to Cheilosis, so D-II.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>So the correct answer is:<br/>\n<br/>A-III, B-I, C-IV, D-II.</p>\n",
    "section": "A"
  },
