    "solution": "A. Saccharin is first popular artificial sweetening agent. It is 550 times as sweet as cane sugar. It is used as intake by diabetic person.<br/><br/>\nB. Aspartame is 100 times as sweet as cane sugar. It is used in cold foods and soft drinks because it is unstable at cooking temperature.<br/><br/>\nC. Alitame is 2000 times as sweet compared to cane sugar. It has excellent stability at high temperature. So, can be used in cooking and baking.<br/><br/>\nD. Sucralose is 600 times as sweet as cane sugar. It is heat stable and finds its use in baked goods.",
